To divide by a fraction, multiply by its reciprocal:

\[
\frac{3}{4}\;\div\;\frac{x}{11}
=\frac{3}{4}\times\frac{11}{x}
=\frac{3\cdot 11}{4\cdot x}
=\frac{33}{4x},
\]
provided \(x\neq0\).

To divide, flip the second fraction and multiply:

\[
\frac{5}{18}\;\div\;\bigl(-\tfrac{15}{24}\bigr)
=\frac{5}{18}\times\Bigl(-\frac{24}{15}\Bigr)
=-\frac{5\cdot24}{18\cdot15}
=-\frac{120}{270}
=-\frac{12}{27}
=-\frac{4}{9}.
\]

